\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Two to three years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was your mother an easy person to talk to, could you you're your worries to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 To her ability of what - what she knew. Or otherwise she used to say - well - I'm a bit doubtful 
on the question - I'll - see your - your grandma Coates, 'cos that was an old lady, she was in some way or other a relative to me - to me mother, but what I could never find out what relative she was to me mother. But she always used to say - wait until I
've been up and seen - your grandma Coates. Then she - 'cos she was one with the - what you might say the knowledge.
