ld she - same as she might say, she greeted everyone of us as we come in, if she was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 She did find it fairly easy to love the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about your dad, was he an e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 sy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 He was a - he was very interes
ted in talking. Specially - if you come for talk about - early - his earlier days when he was in the - in the Militia Guards, Newcastle - the Newcastle and - Royal - Royal - House Guards in London, to the Queen Victoria.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You felt your dad was the kind of person you could confide in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
You could confide in him and he'd give you all his advice. If anything such as - this incident of me - of the wife this last night, he'd do every mortal thing possible to put her at ease. The same if you did - did any
thing - when we were started to work and we - same as I did once, come home with two broken fingers - he repaired 'em up - though I'd been to the doctors, and he - he says, the darned fool, he says, he hasn't set 'em properly. And he - he'd take the splin
ts off and put 'em right and - there you are, he says, you'll be able work couple of days without them splints on now. And he was quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was your dad an affectionate person, did he seem loving towards his wife and family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. My mother can'
t - I - I can't recollect - maybe once I can only recollect him ever picking his fist up to my mother. He - he was - very good at that. He always used to say, a woman's punished enough without being knocked about by her husband. 'Cos his parents used to b
e the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How did he mean a woman's punished enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - a woman's - bearing children and turning in to - turning out to work, caring for the children, looking after the home.
\par 
