\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 He was - he was - he loved music. He really loved music. Well - when he was buried - they come - two relatives from Scotland of
 his and brought two friends - there was Roy Wilton's - Rob Wilton's - eldest sister come with them and one or two other ones of - friends as they - as me father knew as - as knowed me father, they come and - they used the bagpipes for the burial service,
 
when me father died. Or if they come for a - a Christmas party they'd be all there. I know - the people next door, have all - they've all said, well we - are you having your party this time Mr Wilton? Yes. Right. We're off. They' - go to someone else's pa
rty because you couldn't hear your own here once they started.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad didn't encourage you to play the bagpipes or violin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, he didn't - I couldn't - get the hang of it. He did try to learn me to play the - play the bagpipes, 'cos me fingers
 weren't long enough to get at a violin's strings - not to the far string. He did encourage me youngest sister and she took his violin after he - me father died. She had his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 iolin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was your mum musical, did she play anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, well, she - sh
e'd got a - mind you, she'd got a good - tenor voice. And if he was playing anything as she - she knew and liked she used to start off with it. Then the - the other sisters and her sister, me father's brother used to come down when they were all together 
and then there was a real set to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So the family}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176  would sing together, have sing-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 son}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 s, how frequently would this be, would it be once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - me father'd have his violin out every day in the week. He'd sit - he'd sit - weather was like this
 - I've known him go and sit in the back yard under the window - under the living room window, he's token his bagpipe and he's - before he's been - or he's took his violin - before he's been playing ten minutes I'll bet there's been a crowd round the back
 gate listening to him. And they've started singing and dancing up and down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would your parents play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did they play cards or dominoes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh cards and dominoes, yes, draughts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They would put themselves out to amuse you to some degree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - if there were they were books as me father knew was of interest to you and learned you, but otherwise such as - these - sexton Blakes and all like that, no, he
 wouldn't let you read any of that. Anything that was interesting he'd learn you and he'd explain to you what various things were that you couldn't quite graps. When you asked, what does such and such - such a thing mean dad? He'd tell you what - what it 
meant.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about newspapers, did you get a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well we used to always have the News of the World. And the People of the Sunday. The Daily Sketch in the morning and then the Evening Sentinel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you allowed to see the papers when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No. Not until we were - old enough to understand. When we were working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you ever remember your mother or father reading, could they both read and write?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, they could both read and write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And they'd read the newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
We used to see 'em reading perhaps - reading to the elder ones - usyounger ones and we used to sit there listening to what they were saying. They never barred us from that but they wouldn't allow us 
to pick the paper up. If they saw you pick the paper up, what are you going to do with that? Oh I'm going to wrap something up in the back kitchen, some excuse. Yes, well you can put it back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Not in me school days. Only me grandfather. That - and he died in Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Can you remember a funeral up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Up to 1918? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you taken out by your parents to visit neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Relatives but not neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Who would take you out to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 More or less me mother or - and me dad. Just take us once just to show us the - the quicke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 t way to get there and get back again. Then more or less - after then we - used to go on our own. Mother used to say, we
ll, go on you two - you two go and see your Uncle Fred's, you two go to your Uncle Sam's or - perhaps me and our Millie, we used to go regular of a Sunday morning, after school - if there was - if they were decorating and there was no Sunday school they u
sed to say, well go on, you go see your Uncle Sam and then slip along the street - father along the street where they lived in Burslem, see your Uncle Fred. That was - them was me mother's two brothers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you go to the shops with her when you needed shoes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh we'd go to the shop with her and try them on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But food shopping your mum would go and do by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Only o
n one - one - one or two occasions I have been and that - he's taken me to Newcastle to the big allotment as he'd got at - at - Own Clayton Lane there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, what would happen on Bank Holidays, would you 
go to Trenton Gardens or anywhere like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No. No I've never - never known to go anywhere on a holiday,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You didn't go away anywhere to stay on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Can you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Saturdays, well - after was - ten or eleven years of age I used to have a spare time job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Before then you would play around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Play - play around, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you do when you were only ten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well I used to take groceries out. First two hours of 
a Saturday morning - we used to go and deliver meat for the butcher another two hours, then - perhaps another two hours I used to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176  go with the grocer - the greeng}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 rocery man. I used to go with him 'cos more or less it was his donkey and cart as attracted us 
to go round then. 'Course really he was our bandmaster in the Boys Brigade. Sometimes we used to go the Boys Brigade with them. Perhaps they'd go to Silverdale and different places. Well we used to go with them then to the - these does in the Boys Brigade
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So once you were ten you were working most of the time on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - if we were working we used to pick a few coppers up, we used to split half and half, one half used to go to mother and t'other - the other half used to go in your savings box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about Sundays, how would you spend Sundays when were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well we used to have to go to church - to chapel first thing. Then go church - well you used to go Sunday school first thing. Chapel from eleven to twelve. From t
welve until - you see your dinner was ready, you could go wandering around but you'd always got strict orders as soon as you left the house, be car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ful what you're doing in them clothes. Get any dirt on 'em you'll know what tie it is. We used to go - perhaps walk up to Early Woods and round Woolstanton Marsh, by the time we'd come back again down O}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14253099\charrsid2163176 x}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
ford Road and down - Basford Bank and back home again dinner was ready. We had dinner, brushed ourselves up again and off to Sunday school. Then after Sunday sch
ool we used to - play about a bit, well go perhaps - go for a walk round, if the weather was nice, but if it wasn't we used to have to go straight home. Night time we used to have to go to chapel. Me father used to see to that. If you weren't there he'd w
ant to know what was wrong. You had got to be ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Sundays were really given up to chapel going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you have any different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 We all - we had - from weekdays, yes. You never wore the same clothes during the week 
as you did on of a - of a Sunday. Or on special occasions. On special occasions you could wear your best clothes, but as soon as ever you got back again taken off and put away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents expect you to behave differently on a Sunday, were you allowed to go out and play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well if we - if - if we didn't go for a walk round and we wanted to play around we'd got go straight in, change your clothes, put your play - play about clothes on.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would hey let you play football or anything like this on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Not with your best clothes on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents attend a place of worship or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Me mother - me father did. Me father always - was strict on that. But me mother -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Which chapel was it that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The Wesleyan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your mum didn't go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
She went to the - the one right across the road from where we lived. That was the - that was a Methodist chapel. Salem - the Methodist chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad would go to chapel each Sunday would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 He used to go - to the - the Wesleyan chapel down the street, but down the other end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would he go each week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would your mum go each week to the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No. On - just occasionally when she just felt like it she'd go. When
 - most likely she'd go such as - anniversaries. Mother and father used to go together then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well yes. There was always a Sunday school outing and - more or less they used to go to - beach or somewhere like 
that. Or they used to go on a - a boat trip on the canal - on the Golden Canal, 'cos that was when the Golden Canal was in full - use. They used to take us through Trenthan, places like that, Barleston and all round. They used to give you - used to have a
 - a bag with buns and i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
different things, an apple or orange or something like that, while you were going on the boat. But once you got there you sat down at tables put on trestles provided but - paper table cloths. A bottle of lemon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 de or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What other social activities organised by the chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - yes, I was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The Boys Brigade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That was - that belonged to the big church, Etruria - St Margarets church, that belonged to - we used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So if you went to chapel you could go to the church Boys Brigade?
