Well - it was more or less - if there was any functions on of any description and they wanted the Boys Brigade be there we'd got - we were excused from our won Sunday school. We could 
go to that one. Then we used to go - once a month with the Boys Brigade to Silverdale, that was on the Saturday afternoon. Somewhere close to Silverdale - to - supposed to be on a firing course, used to take us - we used to take carbines, of course they w
ere only those little pellets same as you - you shoot at these pairs. But it - that's where I learnt all my army training, through the Boys Brigade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was there a Band of Hope as well?
