\insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
t - me mother hadn't used to bother too much. But me dad - insisted on grace before meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Every night before you used to have - 
have you - see - let me reconstruct the kitchen. Well the kitchen was - the fireplace was here, he'd have you on - on the - the hear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 thrug}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176  there, a rug as used to be homemade rugs, they'd all have to kneel down and say your prayers before going up the stair
s. And then you'd got to say - say them and you'd got to say them loud enough as father could hear you at the bottom of the stairs. He'd shout up, I can't rear so and so saying anything. You'd got to start all over again until every one of us, old and you
ng.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your father take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would he vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Any idea which party he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Labour. That's why I take it from. We're all the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 It would be Liberal at this time, this is pre-1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was there a Labour candidate then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Who was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Macdonald, Ramsey Macdonald.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Why do you think your dad was Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well I don't know, it - it - it seems and appears to me as thought it'
s been a family tradition all the way through, from his parents were Labour for what I can make out. Me mother's side was all Labour. Her aunt - she's got - well I don't - I'm saying she's got - I'm running away with meself there. She's got two sisters as
 used to live up to not so long back. Up to the last five years I'll say when I last heard of them, as used to live in Northwood, Hanley. They were still in the - tailoring business. They were - eeh I was going to tell you that - Maitlands and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But so far as you know both your mum and dad were Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And they would both go and vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They both went to vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would your dad go and listen to political speeches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, he - he'd go and listen to them 'cos they were always - u
sed the ibig square and then the schools, they used to go and sit in the schools and listen to what they were saying and if they got anything to say they used to chime back again and correct 'em. That was when - a chap named Enoch Edwards was putting up f
or the - for Parliament and the Labour Government, and a chap - the other one was the Tory - was - a bloke named Ritner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was this before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. When I was going to school. They used to give us half a day holiday or a day hol
iday from school. The infants, but not the adults. The big girls and the big boys, 'cos the infants were separate. The girls was at the right hand side and the boys were right down at the bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 In some places at this time men felt they risked losing
 their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well no I can't say - 'cos - the firms I worked for and the firms as me father worked for were all Labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So it didn't really arise?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad would vote Labour, he would go and listen to the speeches but so far as you know he didn't actively }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ork for any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 When your parents were not doing their work how would they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
When they weren't at work? Well they - they'd spend their time decorating. Decorating the home and refurnishing - removing things round in the house. They'd - take the girls upstairs and see as 
they scrubbed the rooms and cleaned the - the walls down and most likely me father or - or me mother or perhaps one of the girls'd start decorating the - the rooms, 'cos they weren't paper, only in the front bedrooms, and me father's middle room as they'd
 to any decorating. But the back room, with it being over the back kitchen, was always - kind of colour washed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad also had his garden and he would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And he had his music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would he go out to the pub or anywhere like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Very very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 She never - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did she go out at nights when she came home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 She used to stop in the house. Get - food ready for those as had got to go to work for 'em to take out
 to work. By the time she'd done that all us - the smaller children were all in bed. Biggest part of us more or less, we were all had to be in bed no later than nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your mother have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, not as -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 She would remake clothes for the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right, yes. She - she was a marvel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ous woman for - for remodelling clothes. Out of - she'd make a suit of clothes out of an old overcoat, or an old skirt or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad was working at Shelton in 1911 wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What time would he get home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - being shift work they used to go an six o'clock in the morning 'til two. Then he used to go on at two in the afternoon - when they were on noon shift - 'til ten and then f
rom ten 'til six o'clock the following morning. But - when he come home it was very - if he was on the Shelton Bar he used to come along what they call the Forge Lane and - he used perhaps nip in the back way of the pub and have one half pint or one pint,
 and come out, come home and get his dinner. And then - he'd make -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 He was working three shifts then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6906572\charrsid2163176 Yes. And then he'd }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 most likely go and - have a lie down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 There'd be two weeks when your dad was home in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How many evenings would he spend at home, would he spend his evenings at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well he'd - he'd go down the garden, see as his poultry were all right and see as his garden was all right, 'cos he knew what the children were in the school for climbing over and pinching his stuff if they could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
You said sometimes he would slip in a pub for a pint and other times if he went to a pub it was very irregularly, would your mum go to pubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, not as I sort of recollect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about cock fighting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Oh well that - that - yes, that used to be a regular - a regular do, but - game cocks. Well that'd be take - down by the gardens where - where he used to have his garden. We used to call
 it down the old gardens. Well - it was where - the carters used to empty all the manure from the stables from the horses stables, well - well it kind of made a hollow, like that - well - at the bottom of the hollow they'd get arguing you know and the fir
s
t one'd say, I've got a better gamecock than what yours is. Bring it down. We'll see which is the best. Of course - they'd got to have kind of look-outs to keep their eyes open in case the police come - got; to know and they come down. Then it meant 'em d
oing a double shuffle. 'Cos - they all didn't know the secret ways round.
