\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well we used to go to - two cinemas in Hanley and one in - Newcastle. King and the - the old Tivoli. The place
 as they used to call the bug hut. You walked in but you didn't - you'd no need walk out, you rolled out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. We - what pocket money we got we earned it. Running errands or - doing odd jobs about, different ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And you would give your mum half and you would have the other half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Outside the home? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 It was just the step-daughters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If your mother was ill or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13380718\charrsid2163176 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 onfined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - the church rectory, they used to have a - an old lady as used to come and - attend to them. Now, such as - you needing some old sheeting or something of th
at description - for use for various things, they used to provide at and they always used to come. And that was the rector - the Rector of Etruria church, Mr Barratt, his wife and - her great-aunt. They used to do biggest part of that - apart from - the m
idwife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So this was people attached to the church, not to the chapel that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. The church itself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You were the second eldest in the family, can you remember what happened when either Millie or Hilda or Elsie or Billie was b
orn, would your dad stay at home and help or would the children be packed off to other relatives or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. They were all kept at home. We all mucked in together. One helped one - one another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your parents did have relatives living nearby and that you would visit them both with your parents and later on you would go by yourself?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And they would come to your house as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You said they came at Christmas and times like this? Did they come at othe times throughout the year or just special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well, yes - mother had got one brother as used to work on Wedgewoods until - on Joseph Wedgewood's place, and he used to call - twice or three times a week before going home, to his own home in Cobridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Your dad's relatives would be in Scotland would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - with being up in Scotland I only saw me grandmother and grandfather - well two - twice I - I think. And the whole time as they were alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So the parents relatives who were living round about here were your mother's relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - me mother had got - these two brothers, one as used to work on - on Wedgewood's and the other one used to work on the same firm where she was - a dipper. Yes. She used to work on the same firm as hi
m. And then - she got - two sisters as were - Maitlands and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And they lived in the neighbourhood as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, they didn't live in the neighbourhood, they lived in Bucknell. Same with her other eldest sister - her other sister, the one youn
ger than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And you'd see them fairly frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh yes, yes, yes. But - the two sisters as used to - live in Northwood, I've not seen them - how long -s
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They won't be living now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They won't - maybe and maybe no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How frequently would you see them in your childhood?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
h we used to see them very often. Very very often. That's where me mother used to get biggest part of her garment stuff, for making dresses or suits of clothes for the boys. Or anyone else if they bought the stuf
f to her she'd sit and make a suit of clothes while you were looking at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - yes, there was plenty of friends round about the neighbourhood where we lived. Everybody seemed to be friendly with one another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were they neighbours first who then became friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your mum and dad have the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well, yes. But me father never mixed too much with them. He was more -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was it the women who would visit houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well they ne
ver used to make it a - a - a regular - what you might say calling it a open house. No, he wouldn't - me father wouldn't have that. If there was anything wrong we could always just nip - go and ask Mrs so and so come - come - mother wants to see her. And 
them sort of occasions, yes, dad'd let them in. But he wouldn't - same as they used to come in and sit gossiping instead of doing their own work, he said they were neglecting their own home to come and sit gossiping because me mother was always at work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13380718\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
men wouldn't come to the house to see your dad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So if people did come in your dad would have preferred them to come in by invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 By invitation, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If people did come in would they be given anything to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - not in liquor form. They'd - mother'd always - or me dad'd give 'em - til one of the girls or might ask - say to mother, pour so and so a drink of tea out. Would you like a piece of seed cake? Or - coconut cake, currant cake or anything li
ke that. Homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Thi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13380718\charrsid2163176 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
 would happen when people came in at any time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But they weren't invited in for set meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Set meals were kept to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The friends who came in, would you say they were more your mother's friends or your father's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well yes, you could - you could say that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That they were your mother's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They were more me mother's friends than what they were me father's friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No, I can't say. Perhaps - perhaps once occasionally they'd go - in the neighbourhood but not out of the neighbourhood. We always knew where to find them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 People often tell us that in those days they made t
heir own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours, did your dad take his violin with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - he - he never without ot. I can't see why they didn't - put it in his coffin when he died,
 'cos he was never without it, it was as much attached to his violin as what he was to his pipe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Could he play popular tunes on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 He could play any mortal thing. No matter what you asked him to play he'd play it. The popular tunes then. Such a
s - the pop music as Gertie Getani you see and all like that, and he could play them standing on his head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class 
and some to another? Were you aware that everybody wasn't living the same kind of life that you were at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I can't say that, I think people were all classed - they all seemed to class theirselves one with the other. Never one -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You 
weren't aware that there were some people who were terribly poor and that there were some people who were better off, the ladies from the rectory, did you see them as being on a different level to what you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well we always worked on a - the same 
level as one another. We never - if we could - such as saying, if we could help anyone in the lower class we used to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But you would acknowledge that there was a lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How would you have divided it then, there was the lower class that you didn't think you belonged to and then you were in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No. No. I can't say as we didn't belong to 'em, we - we were all classed more or less with the people. No we - if we got a pair of shoes as - another one was a bi
t down - the short side we - mother used to say - or me dad used to say, take these up to - such a place, up Salem Street, tell 'em your dad - your mother and father have sent them, ask them if they'll fit one of their children. We used to all be friendly
 with one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If you had to describe yourself as belonging to a certain class what class would you have described yourself as belonging to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 A middle class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What sort of people belonged to the same class as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well they were all 
working class people. All of us. Everyone was no better off than - never reckoned one no better off than what the others was. Apart from the - the factory owners, such as Jess Shirley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about people like teachers and the Rector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, he was just a common - common man just same as yourself. Old Barratt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were there certain people you would salute to or touch your cap to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - that was respect more or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you show this respect to everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Yes. We all - we were all brought up, I thin, in the same community of - respect - respect of - respect thy neighbour as you respect yourself. That was the thing as we father drilled into us from the Bible three times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was there anyone in the neighbourhood who you called sir or master, anybody who everybody looked up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - only - such as Jess Shirley or - or the Vicar, we always used say sir to h
im. Or Jess Shirley, 'cos he was a - one of the prominent - Cowleys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13380718\charrsid2163176 haws}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
 and Walkers, they were a foundry, they lived down at the bottom and of Etruria, they were - we used to say - if we had to approach them for anything whatsoever we always used - touch us - us caps and say sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you acknowledge that they were living on a different plane to what most folk were living on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 In the district where you lived then they were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How would you come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - Mr Shirley and - CowleyShaws and Walkers, they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13380718\charrsid2163176 
used to use the same place of w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 orship as what we did, that's how we kept - how we got in contact with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Why were they considered important, because they'd got money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They'd got money and they'd got factories and - various other things like so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you have considered that shopkeepers were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. Shopkeepers were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And you considered that the clergy were fairly ordinary too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Teachers were - as - as lived in the district more or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What about farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - farmers, there was only one farmer in the district, that was Clarkes down at the bottom of Etruria Woods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you feel about them, did you think that they were well off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, they - they were just the same, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And the employers were the ones that were considered to be important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The employers were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What 
sort of people would you say went to church, you were usually going to chapel, were you conscious that the people who went to church were of a different kind, in some places the factory owners and rich folk went to church and working class went to chapel?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No. I can't say that 'cos - now Cowleyshaws and Walkers, Clarkes the farmers, they used to go to the Wesleyan chapel. Oh ahd - old Jess Shirley and his family, they all went to the one Wesleyan chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you lived did all the people in the wo
rking class have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No, they were all in the same working class group. Everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You felt that everyone had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you weren't conscious that there were some rough families and some that were more respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well yes, there was some rough families. But - they always used to regard them - and not - not class them lower as you might say you s
hould walk outside and tread on 'em or push 'em down, no, we used to help to lift one another up, as far as funds of anything else'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember people making a distinction if somebody's father was a craftsman and somebody else's father was a 
labourer, would this make any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. None whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I can't say as they had any different opinions. No, I think me father always used to say,
 no one was no better than what another one was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But you felt your mum and dad were in agreement, they would look on people in the same light?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to any particular social class? If sh
e had had to describe herself would she have said she was working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Working class. Yes, she never classed herself any different, only working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Why would she describe herself as working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - she described herself as work
ing class because she turned out - she wasn't frightened of turning out to work. She worked for every crust of bread as she - as she ate or her children ate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well if they were lucky enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you know anybody who was so lucky?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No, I can't say as I do. I think - everybody if they were - wherever they moved and you happened to come over 'em again you - you'd see as they was still in the same position as they were when they left you - left your district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But you think it might have been possible to move from working class to something hieher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Because - I've seen times when various ones - various neighbours could - if they'd have worked it - the proper way rou
nd as they could have made theirselves better and more important than what they really were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How would they have achieved this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well because - the better jobs. Better education. Went a good way with it. And they could - step out of one place and
 go higher up into another one for one reason - there's Mr - Mr Moore on - on Wedgewoods, he was just an ordinary caster.- vases and teapots, fancy tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5009593\charrsid2163176 -po}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ts, v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5009593\charrsid2163176 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
ses - fancy vases. He was an ordinary caster, and he - he said as he wasn't going to be a - an o
rdinary caster, earn his money, he was going to have people to work for him to earn his money for him. And he did do and he achieved that. He went to - eeh - somewhere in England I know. He went and he - and he did better for himself. And the last as I he
a
rd of him he's already made better and his family had improved and they're still carrying on the firm, of Moore's factory. He started his own - from - from a little kitchen as you might say, like this. And he started building up and building up until he g
ot a factory going. And he got people working for him. Earning - earning money for him, not him earning money for keep somebody else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady in these times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Only - Mr and Mrs Shirley. And Mr and Mrs Coates, Cowleyshaws and Walkers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They were factory owners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They - they were factory owners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Why would people describe them as being real gentlemen and real ladies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - with them being factory owners they could 
put their hand in their pocket and pull a two bob piece out or - where you couldn't put your hand in your pocket and pull a farthing out - farthing out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Remember seeing a policeman around? Oh yes, we saw them very very often. Policemen were - well they lived in the district more or less.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They were part of the district scene rather than coming because there was trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you think of the policeman when you saw him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well we - a protector of the law. We - of course if we saw a policeman we used to say, oh what's gone wrong? Something gone wrong somewhere - there's a policeman dodging about. Or - it was perhaps be just routine work, s
ame as the wife said on her - on her talk - as - in - to communicate with one policeman to another. - they used-three taps on the kerbstone and it - my word it had used to travel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If you were naughty would your mother threaten you with the policeman, would she say, I'll call the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - she used to try to frighten us that was, I'll run you up to the Nanley - Town Hall. If you don't - if you don't be a good boy I'll - I will - I'll send for Bobby Boston to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 went to the schools. An
d from the schools they used to send us to Oldham and Burkes's down Sadlers Cottages down bottom of Etruria and she used to prepare - a hot dinner for people what were really in need. Mind you, the Education Committee used to grant so much for that one pe
rson.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So this would be what the children would get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You didn't get money from any charities or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No, none whatsoever. Not to my knowledge anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You said that your mum had had to go out work more or less all her married life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Because your mother and father accepted that one wage wasn't sufficient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
One wage wasn't sufficient to keep us going. 'Cos there was - with the family being - a big mixed family. The elder ones were taking more really to keep than what the younger ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You mentioned this one occasion when you went to this woman to have a meal, how did you feel about going fown there, did you feel ashamed?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - no - 'cos I used to - same as you see look round to see if anybody was watching but soon as she spotted you and she }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5009593\charrsid2163176 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 aw you on the nervous side she used to come to you, now come on young fellow, let me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5009593\charrsid2163176 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176  take}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5009593\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
you in. There's nothing as I'm going to do for you as is in anyway disgraceful. You get your dinner. 'Cos the f
irst time I went in - I couldn't - of course not only me, me other sisters went in as well. We couldn't sit down and see children in a worse position really, more poorer than what we were on the whole, taking it on the whole, without. We used to take them
 down and we used to - Mrs Burkes' - give him my dinner. I can manage 'til teatime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If there were poor children why weren't they getting the food, who decided who should go down to Mrs Burkes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well this - the Education committee knew as these chi
ldren as wouldn't be granted a meals meat from Mr Burkes as because the parents - both mother and father - the elder - they'd got elder brothers and sisters, they - what you might say they squandered the money away instead of looking after the children's 
bellies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So they decided there was the deserving poor and the undeserving poor?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
We sacrificed our dinner - more - not every day but once perhaps - you were only granted these free dinners once a week in a week one week and you'd got to have a br
eak, then - the schoolteacher - the headmaster used to say, well it's your turn now. How many of you? Well you used to tell him how many of you you and your sisters or brothers, whoever they were, tell him how many there were and he used to send you down.
 You go down today. Tomorrow you two to go down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So she would prepare a certain number of dinners every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Every day she prepared enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But there were a lot of children who could have done with that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But she prepared a certain number of meals and they sent down that many children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Irrespective of how many kids of benefited from having that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's right. Yes. Well - the grocery shops, the butchers shops, the butchers ad -t he - bakeries, s
hops and all like that what sold tea and sugar and all that, then there was a green }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176 vegetable shop and there was a f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
ish shop, the butchers, they all used to send so much stuff down each week to prepare - to provide for a certain amount of children at that 
- for that. And yet the - the school Education Committee should have stood one part of it. 'Cos they did get their half, the - the people as provided the stuff, they go their half but it - the - extras were pushed off so as the children'd get - perhaps ge
t
 an extra couple of - half a dozen boys and girls for another dinner. Now she couldn't get 'em in such as - say - yesterday dinner time, she couldn't get 'em all down. She'd say, well those as haven't had anything today, come down tomorrow and I'll get yo
u your dinner. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 About how many would she be able to provide for each day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - two dozen. Per day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How many children out of your class would be receiving free dinners at that time, most of them or just a few of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Out of my - out of mine - there was four of us was allowed down, every other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would that be twenty going down out of your class over a period of time or were there only four altogether that would go down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, there'd be four - as the classes run down, that was from standard seven - ex-
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But you saw them too frequently to be terrified of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Yes. He was too big a - he loved children too much. He wouldn't - run a child in for - for any little thing, same as they would today. He'd rather help them than -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you think at this time that police treated people well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They treated people in the proper respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, oh very very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did he live in the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Not many yards away from where we lived. He kept a public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were your parents able to pay the rent, you didn't get into arrears?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No. That was one thing my dad wouldn't have allowed. He said, we'll go 
without a meals meat for a weeks meat - a weeks food before missing the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you have any strong feelings about the landlord, was he a good landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. If there was any improvements as you wanted doing he'd have them done for you. 'Cos h
e always used to say, and his wife used to say, 'cos the old devil died, left his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
wife the house or the property and - he used - he always used to say to us, if there was anything wanted altering or improving it used to put a bigger price on the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well I will - I won't say as they didn't, 'cos there was times - there were times as things were very difficult. Now - we'll say such as - me dad being taken ill. He - he 
was the same as me, he wouldn't - he - he'd go to work if they had to carry him back again. Perhaps hadn't earned enough money and things had gone a bit on the stiff side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How would you cope, did you have to get help from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. Only
 once. Once. And we didn't go to the Guardians for that help. We seven, seven, six, ex-six, five, four, three, two and then the first standard coming up from the infants school and there was the infants school, they didn't go in classes more or less, they
 did go in a kind of a class but there's only three classes in the infants, three age groups and the same happened in the girls school. But they only run up to standard six in the girls school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So each day only four children could go from the class th
at you were in, but if you went round the class how many of them could have benefited from that dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Oh - one third of them, out of every class - could have - afforded - could have done with that meals meat before they was what would do for go down. I've refused mine many a time, purpose to let - someone else go, such as - well I won't mention names.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 When there was somebody in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly did they have any special way of showing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well, not as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You don't remember any particular families that were looked sonw on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Nobody lived so badly, who were drunken or spent their money wrongly that other folk felt they needed to take action against them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 There was Brac
es, Charlie Brace and he - him - after the first - after the first world war he seemed to - have jumped up that lad did. Oh pre - well the Braces family in Savelly Street, they were really - down on their rock bottom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How would people let them know that they looked down on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I've seen 'em going with the - the lads with their trouser backsides out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
If you live in a street that's fairly respectable and you get somebody that doesn't conform to the standards of the neighbourhood people won't talk to them, they won't help them, were you conscious that this was ever done to a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, they always used to try to help. We'd help 'em as far as - funds and possibilities would do, they'd go and give 'em adv}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ce of how to carry on, try to put
 'em on the right way to making good. To bringing themselves up - to try to tidy themselves up, 'cos it did happen with two or three - them and the Newtons. They did - improve theirselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you given lessons by your parents, a tutor or a governess?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, we had teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 When you first started school what time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What time did you get back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Half past twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 When you started school at four would you go for the full day, morning and afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And afternoon school would start at two o'clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Two o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And when would you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What kind of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - it was a - a very nice school, it was a County Council school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was it mixed, did you have boys and girls there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 In the infants, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Then did it split up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Then after you went out of the - the infants into the first standard in the -
 the big school as they called 'em there was all boys one side, girls the other. In different schools. The schools were altogether, joined together - the three schools, the infants were in the middle. The girls school was on the - the right hand side and 
the boys was on the left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 hand side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Walk it, it wasn't many yards away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How long did it take to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Three minutes. I could spit at it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did anybody take you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well we were - while we were in the infants we - the elder sisters used to take us to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But after that it was near enough for you to make your own way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And you used to come home for your midday meal - what did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well the first week or suchlike - first month we'll say - we - we - I didn't like school. But after - me father'd had us and were talking to us in a - same as they would do talking to a child, encouraged us along, well my goodness me we be
 stepping standards. And we weren't long before we were - we were standing in one class two years, before I could move up into the - the big schools as they called it. Then you went into the first standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you were quite bright then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well for a - for a start off, yes. I can't say as - I were - I was a dunce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you like about school, which lessons did you like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - we - I used to like the geography lessons more or less. 'Cos - sums or anything like that it seemed to - bore
 me more than anything else, 'cos the teacher'd be there with his chalk on the blackboard, scribbling here and putting - comma's and question marks all round the place - U used fall asleep sometimes watching him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 But geography interested you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I - I was mad on geography.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What was so fascinating about geography?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well they used talk about - different animals and - various parts of the country. How to cope with various people in various - from various countries. What would you do and how w
ould you like it, then they'd perhaps give you a map to try to trace. 'Cos you'd always got a map in your geography book. I - I do believe I've got one now, somewhere in the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you think about your teachers, were you fond of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well, yes, I only had one - dopey teacher. He was in - in the first standard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Once you were split up between boys and girls were you taught by all men then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. All men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What was wrong with the teacher in standard one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - he was 
- named - same name as her maiden name, Coxen, lived up - not - he didn't live a great way, in South Street. Now he - he was dozey, he used sit talking to you - the morning had gone before you could say as you'd learnt anything. So - when the head teacher
,
 the headmaster come down, we used to call him Boswhite, when he come down and - you were going through your exams to see which was going up or which were going to stay down in standard one. Well that's how he found out as we weren't being - taught proper
l
y. 'Course he didn't mind, he showed us - when you went into the next standard he was a Duke as was taking our class 'cos he was a real tartar, he could - he'd drill it into you if he got a hammer and chisel. He'd make you learn it. Then - you - 'cos he r
un two classes together, --standard two and three. Then the - the next one used to run four and five. Each teacher took two classes, 'cos you were divided by the partition right down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was this because there weren't enough teachers to have one each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That's it, yes. And they hadn't got - the school wasn't large enough to take more classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You mentioned there was six and six ex, what did six ex mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - it's - that was - was caused through - with the - the same as I say, there wasn't 
enough - enough room for the classes to be made - so they called 'em class - class six and class ex six, seven and ex-seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I thought they might have been split up according to ability, you had the brighter children in one class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - in ex -
 in standard six and then you went up into standard ex-six. That was in - the same classroom but on the other side of the class and from that one you went into standard seven, that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176 o}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ld man Glover. 'Cos he was our - music master. He was our music master
 as well. He - he took standard seven and ex-seven. Well if you passed out through those two, if your parents could afford it you got your - your chance of going into an High School, if you wished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did many people go on and do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh yes, there was quite a few as went up into - into the High School, that was up in Hanley, where the big multi-storey shops are now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you have liked to have gone and done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I was quite contented as I was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life, did they put stress on good manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - standard five, he was a teacher as believed in - in good behaviour, good manners, knowing how to speak to your elders. That was old Gibbins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did they emphasise things like tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. He liked you - he liked to see your desk as clean when you left it as what it was when you went to it first thing in the morning.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did the teachers insist that you shoul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15362748\charrsid2163176 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176  be punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 We'd got to be punctual. Or you get your - your red mark beside your name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would they correct the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. They'd tell you how to talk. And they'd drill -t into you until you knew how to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - he'd have you at front of the class and he'd have you - correct - making the correction up as best as you could, if it was outside school he'd have you and he'd give you a - a real good lecture, and he'd have you in front of the class an
d you - you'd face the class and you - you - he'd tell you what you really were or what you should have done or what you shouldn't have done. He used to - there wasn't the cane - very often used unless it was a real case of - necessity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What was a case of necessity then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - if you'd done something as - you knew very well as you - you hadn't ought to have done. Same as we got one or two - very bad pupils in the school, in the class, and one, he was - he was a real dud, how he ended up in life 
I don't know, but he was a real dud when he left school and he never moved from standard four, from the time he got to it to the time he was old enough to leave it. He used to be one as'd - rip pages out of - exercise books, fold it up and - float it and 
-
 and he always dipped it in the inkwell and floated it so it'd hit the teacher the back of the neck when he was doing it - anything on the board. And he was the only one as I've heard - as I know to - as went to the headmaster's room to be caned. 'Cos the
y - he used to give it to you on your left and right hand than give it to you across your backside. 'Course his father didn't give a damn whether he pulled out or pulled in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork, your dad obviously did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - yes, he - 'cos you took your school report every term.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They'd discuss it with you would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And - they'd sign it and say they agreed with - the teacher's judgement, the head teachers judgement on you - your progress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would your parents ever go to the school and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Not unless there was something - something wrong as had been said as wasn't true, concerning one of other of the girls or the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Can you remember your mum or dad ever going to the school for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did the other children at the school come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, they all - some of them really as you'd - if you'd have seen them coming to school you'd have thought they'd come off - the Du
ke of Gloucester's people, 'cos they come from top end of Basford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You mean they were well dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
They were well dressed, but they - they were more well dressed than what they were mannered. They couldn't tell - they couldn't speak to you in a proper civil voice. A civil tongue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Where did Shirley's children go to school, they didn't go to the local school? The factory owner's children, where would they go to school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - they've always gone to - to the same school, but if anybody's
 done any - anything out of place, any wrong, they've always send em to - Wellington Reformatory school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would the factory owners children go to the local council school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh yes, to - 'til they passed their school - exams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 In some places they would have gone to private schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Not. - not unless - no, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 As far as you knew they went to the local council school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 They went to the council - the local county council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No, no. No, I think all my - the teachers as I was under in the Etruria school all seemed to work out the same. They all - 'cos they were all - you might say they were all on the same lives and the same standards as ourselves, the
y couldn't - they weren't higher than what a - didn't class themselves higher than what you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did they make favourites of the brighter children perhaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No No, I can't say as they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No, no. If there were - if there were they'd be fighting amongst theirselves one minute, next minute they - they'd be there - the head teacher'd have in - you've to make friends straight away. And the - same as you see them on the telly, they'd be loving 
one another next minute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were there any children who were left out of things, were the poor children looked down on or perhaps the physically handicapped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Or perhaps kids who weren't too bright, would they be left out of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. They were all - all classed in one game. All classed the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was this the only school you ever went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 That was the only school as I ever went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Twelve.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you have stayed on any longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
If I'd have had the opportunity yes, maybe I'd have stopped on until the proper age of leaving school at fourteen. Fourteen - thirteen or fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Then why did you leave when you were twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - re
ally - it wasn't as we - we'd got - we had - we couldn't leave the school, it was a case we'd got to leave it because - there wasn't room, the children were coming up that quickly, they couldn't put any more in. And the nearest schools were too far away f
o
r sending them from their present homes. Well the parents wouldn't allow them to go - to a - a school too far away. And such as sending them to - a Shelton school, well they'd got a more - more children there than what they could really cope with so - the
 only thing as they did was - give different ones - if you wished, could leave school. 'Cos there wasn't many as refused it. Soon as they were asked if they wanted to leave school when they were twelve we were allowed to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You didn't go to evening classes or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well no, not on the whole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If you had your time to come over again would you try to do things differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I would try to have done things differently if I got me time to come all over again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You would have stayed on at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I would have stayed on at school and carried on and I'd have encouraged anyone else as was interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What would you have hoped to do if you had stayed on at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well I should have tried to have got into the very top standard, and then got - transferred to a - to an High School where - or a Technical school where - of were there was one as had been started up the top of Basford Bank, just at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What kind of a job would you have seen that leading to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - I had at that time got me mind built on colour mixing, 'cos me father - with me father being a colour mixer and he 
- he gave me - he left me the books as he'd used for colour mixing, when he - when me dad died he left me these books and I goes and gives 'em away and they were worth - taking on the whole - they wer worth at least - three hundred pound for the value of 
'em. And today I don't think they - they can now grasp the idea of mixing the blue jasper. 'Cos you can see the glaze rose in it. Where my dad had got it to that perfection as the glaze hardened and never moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 If your dad enjoyed colour mixing at Wedgewood's why did he go to Shelton, was it more money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 It was more money you see, going to Shelton Bar than what it was on there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - I did - did do until - I got the misfortune of gettin
g me brains knocked about in the - first world war. No, there was nothing really as got in me way there. I could - talk same as the remainder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You had a part time job while you were at school more or less from when you were ten, you were delivering bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Bread and groceries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And greengroceries because you liked the man with the donkey and cart, how did you get these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - with mother - dealing with the shops and - with the grocery shop, she asked me - she asked mother if - me m
other when mother went down to get some groceries, if I'd like to - earn a - a copper or two. A couple or three bob - to - help me out as it'd be able to - I'd be able to put it to one side for when I start -s properly work. Well I - I did this job and th
en -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you be paid as much as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well I - I got - I used to get two chilling or half a crown for taking the bread out for the full week to different places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you could take it out each day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Each night, I used to run her these errands, taking groceries and things from just around about the district, close by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What time would you be working from, this was after you got home from school at four?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh well, it'd take me about an hour. Or an hour and a half to do the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You weren't doing the bread and the groceries and the greengrocery all at the same time, they were different jobs spread over time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Well I used to do me greengrocery business on more of a weekends. Such as of a Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The bread was a regular job throughout the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Do you think that these part time jobs and the bit of independence you got from having them, did they affect your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - yes, in a way. When I started doing that I thought 
to myself, shan't I be glad now when I've finished school altogether, as I can go and get a - a proper job. Or when it did come to the time as I'd left school -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Which year was it that you left school, would this be 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Can you remember what month it would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well it'd be - the last week in October in 1911 when I - I left school. I went - after I - I was told to go after a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Who told you to go after one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 A full time job more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Who told you to go for the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - someone - a youngster that used to work for 'm and he'd got a - he got older and he got a better job to go to. And he said - he said, dost - dost want a steady job? I say, aye. Why - where is there one? He said, well take your birth cert
 - take your - leaving school certificate with you and go up to - Macpherson Street, Jack Waines and tell him as I've told you to come. He said, well I shall be there. Anyway, he says, you go up and get it. So I went up. 'Course wages weren't much in them
 days. I used to get there at eight o'clock in the morning and never knowed what time I was going to get home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was Jack Waines the grocers chop you were telling me about?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, a green - a grocery - just a grocery shop. It had used to be a 
place where they used to bake their own bread when the other proprietor kept it, Mr Coates. - He used to bake his own bread, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you started work at half past eight in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 We used to start at eight o'clock in the morning. Never knowed what time I was getting home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You were telling me that sometimes you were out delivering at ten and eleven o'clock at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Twelve o'clock at night many a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You worked right through from eight o'clock in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. Sometimes he - he used to give me a bit of tea or something like that for to carry me through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you get your dinner at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I used to have to take me food with me really. But I be going to take me own tea, but they always used to bring me a
 little bit so - when I'd finished all me own errands running and - looking - cleaning and running up to the - bakeries fe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6435091\charrsid2163176 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
ching cakes and etcetera up -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You would have described your job as an errand boy at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. I was just an errand boy. Well I used to go fetch up from the warehouse - whole}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6435091\charrsid2163176 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
ale warehouses I used to go, take a truck up with a box on, bring in sugar or - if they hadn't delivered it - different other commodities as they wanted, they used to give me a list. I used to go to
 that one - that was Dan Lewis's. Or done to the other one was more of - that was another grocery place, they used to have salt and all like that. That was S}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6435091\charrsid2163176 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 mons, that wasn't many yards from the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Were you working six days a week at this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
No. Oh on a Thursday. It was supposed to have been a half day Thursday but I was more or less working. Yes, always found me something to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How much wage were you paid?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - it used to run about - five shillin
g a week. That was - the most as I ever got from him. Well - different days, such as Wednesdays - Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Fridays I used to have to take these big journeys to the far end of Dresden. Well - I'd got to wait until one of the grocery men - o
n
e of the bread men was - as delivered bread to this grocers for him to call. Well he used to come to the shop with his horse and cart - horse and van and he used to take me to Dresden, near enough to Dresden, well the remainder part I'd got to walk myself
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Dresden is another part of Stoke is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Right at the other end of Monkton, far end of Monkton. Well he took me - he took me as far as that - that was as far as he went 'cos their bakery was there. Well he used to drop me off there and I'd got g
o - he showed me where the place was as I'd got to deliver the first lot of groceries and bread. Then I'd got wak from there then to another place, close to - in - just outside Longton, this side Longton, and I got walk from there and come all the way bac
k
 again. That brought me past the North Stafford Royal Infirmary as is now. Along Princes Road. Well I've got call at the people where - as own - used to own this shop. And when I knocked 'em up, he said, has he sent you out at this time of the night again
,
 he says, I shall have to have a damned word with him about this business. But it made no difference, I used to have to go and it used to be twelve o'clock when I was delivering groceries there. Well there's - been many a night as it's been thundering and
 lightning and I've took no notice. I wasn't a bit afraid. I used to go marching to the - right to the very end against Ordsell church and I used to cut down the side walk - a lady}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6435091\charrsid2163176 \rquote s }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 walk as they used to call it, but it used to bring me at top of - across the wooden bridge and - top of Brickillen Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You were only twelve when you were doing all this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you think it was a fair wage that you were being paid for all this amount of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - same as me mother and father said, it
 was getting too much keeping you out at that time of the night. But - it was a break in - to break you in to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you have holidays with pay from this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No. No, it wasn't out then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you do with thi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 s five bob you got, did you hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176  it over to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Would you get some of it back?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - perhaps give me a shilling, cos a shilling was a - a shilling was the same as a ten shilling in these times or - or more than that really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How did you get on with the people you worked with, were there a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 n}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 other people in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, there was only the - the proprietor, and his wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you were very much on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. I was always on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh - what? I wouldn't work for him again, not if he - his hair hung in gold and he give me every bit as he combed out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you think about the job itself, did you like the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I didn't like the job, it - but I was glad just to take it on temporary. Until I was old enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How long did you work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 About two years. I was fourteen years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Then what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I think it was about twelve months to - twelve months or so. Anyway - well when I become get
 older, up to thirteen years of age I went to - I left him, I told him I wasn't coming no more. Well me mother called as she was going to work. And told him as I wasn't going to com}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176  no more for that money. Well I - I got a job on Johnson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 s.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What did you do at Johnson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 s?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
Well - we was called - dottlers. We used to help the places out. We were only lads, we used to help 'em draw and get the wolsaggers dressed and ready for - for them to place the ware in for putting in the ovens. Well, with being 
under age every time as they got the wire from the office as - the works inspector was on - we used to have to make ourselves scarce until he'd gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What age would you have to be legally to work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Fifteen. Fourteen to fifteen. Well we were
 working under age so we had to make ourselves scarce, go round ovens, go round anywhere out the way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Weren't you allowed in potteries at all at that age or was it just this particular job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 This particular job, we could have gone and worked in 
the gloss warehouse or the gloss - or the biscuit warehouse, or the biscuit - the biscuit warehouse but 'course this job was - the dust was laden with lead - lead poison. You see, we weren't allowed to go in it until you were age fifteen, and then you had
 to pass the doctor to see as you were fit enough to carry on the job. See you hadn't got to pass the doctor before then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How frequently would factory inspectors come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - he'd perhaps come every three months or every four months. Just according how many factories he'd got to visit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 The employers felt it was worth the risk, they didn't mind that you were working under age, you hadn't gone in and preten}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ed to be older, they knew how old you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, they knew how old we were by our birth certificate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 This was a sort of deceit that they were carrying on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. They - they were carrying on like this and they knew if they were - we were catched they'd be in trouble wit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 h it for employing us in the sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ger house - under age. Same with the girls in the dipping house, they had to skedaddle out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What hours did you work while you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - yes, dottler - well, that was more or less from half past seven in the morning 'til half past five. That all -
 that all depend how you worked, if you got - if we got a stint in - see - if they drawed a whole - they drawed - they'd got to put so much work in to make a days wages up. Well if we finished at four o'clock, if the place was finished at four o'clock we 
could finish if we wanted, but we used to stop 'til five to half past straightening the sag}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 
racks up, getting it all ready for - for the next days work. by the time as we - take to go the drunken thimbles and things out. We could be ready for the next morning, we should have things more comfortabl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 e, we could get done more quick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 ly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Was this five days a week or did you work Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Six days - five days and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 You worked Saturday morning?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Saturday morning up to - twelve o'clock. Twelve to half past. Half past twelve was the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 What rate of pay did you have for this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Fifteen shilling a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you think that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 A real damn good wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Even though it was a dangerous job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes. It was a real damned good wage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How much of that would you give to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Well - perhaps mother'd give me half a crown, three bob out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 And the money you handed over to your mother went into family expenditure for the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 While you were working at Johnson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16347937\charrsid2163176 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 s you were working with more people, you weren't on your own as you had been previously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 No, I was working with more people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Did you enjoy this more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 I enjoyed it more than anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 So you liked the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1265594 WW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 Oh I - I - yes. I was contented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598081 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2966169\charrsid2163176 How long did this job last?
